.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-BACKUP" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-backup \- export a portable JSON snapshot of the wallet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-backup
.RB [ --output
.IR file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Exports the active wallet to JSON: account list (address, description,
balance, dates) and the most recent 1000 ledger entries.
.PP
Without
.B --output
the snapshot is written to stdout.  With
.B --output FILE
it is written to
.IR file
and a short confirmation
.nf
{"ok":true,"file":"FILE"}
.fi
is printed to stdout.
.PP
The snapshot can be used as a read-only audit trail or as source
material for a manual restore.  It does not contain private keys or
API keys.
.TP
.B --output FILE
Write the snapshot to
.I FILE
instead of stdout.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-stats (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-user (1)
